# User Stories

## Users

### Sign Up

* As an unregistered and unauthorized user, I want to be able to sign up for the website via a sign-up form.
  * When I'm on the `/signup` page:
    * I would like to be able to enter my email, with my preferred username and password on a form.
    * I would like the website to log me in upon successful completion of the sign-up form and direct/redirect me to the home page.
  * When I enter invalid data on the sign-up form:
    * I would like the website to inform me of the validations I failed to pass, and repopulate the form with my valid entries (except my password).
    * So that I can try again without needing to refill forms I entered valid data into.

### Log in

* As a registered and unauthorized user, I want to be able to log in to the website via a log-in form.
  * When I'm on the `/login` page:
    * I would like to be able to enter my email and password on a clearly laid out form.
    * I would like the website to log me in upon successful completion of the lob-up form.
      * So that I can seamlessly access the site's functionality
  * When I enter invalid data on the log-up form:
    * I would like the website to inform me of the validations I failed to pass, and repopulate the form with my valid entries (except my password).
      * So that I can try again without needing to refill forms I entered valid data into.

### Demo User

* As an unregistered and unauthorized user, I would like an easy to find and clear button on both `/login` pages to allow me to visit the site as a guest without signing up or logging in.
  * When I'm on either the `/login` pages:
    * I can click on a Demo User button to automatically log me in as a user so that I could test the functionalities of the website

### Log Out

* As a logged in user, I want to access a log out button that is easy to find on the profile button drop down menu on the navigation bar.
  * While on any page of the site:
    * I can log out of my account and be redirected to the home page.
      

## Reviews on Restaurants

### Create Reviews

* As a logged in user, I want to be able to post new FauxTweets.
  * When I'm on the `/new-fauxtweet` page:
    * I can write and submit a new FauxTweet.
      * So that I can share my thoughts and memes with my friends.

### Viewing Yelp Reviews/Restaurants

* As a logged in _or_ logged out user, I want to be able to view a feed of the restaurants that have had the most recent reviews posted on them .
  * When I'm on the `/restaurants` page:
    * I can view the 15 most recently reviewed restaurants.
      * So that I can read about how good the restaurant experience was

* As a logged in _or_ logged out user, I want to be able to view a specific restaurant and its associated reviews and favorites.
  * When I'm on the `/restaurants/:id` page:
    * I can view the content of the restaurant, as well as the associated reviews and favorites.
      * So that I can read and interact with the other reviews of the restaurant, and add my own thoughts and decide if I want to add this to my favorites list.

### Updating Reviews

* As a logged in user, I want to be able to edit my reviews by clicking an Edit button associated with the review anywhere that review appears.
  * When I'm on the `/restaurants`, `/restaurants/:id`, or `/users/:id/reviews` pages:
    * I can click "Edit" to make permanent changes to reviews I have posted.
      * So that I can fix any errors I make in my reviews

### Deleting Reviews

* As a logged in user, I want to be able to delete my reviews by clicking a Delete button associated with the reviews anywhere that reviews appears.
  * When I'm on the `/restaurants`, `/restaurants/:id`, or `/users/:id/reviews` pages:
    * I can click "Delete" to permanently delete a reviews I have posted.
      
